b'This is wonderful, but not enough. Please be safe out there. Get vaccinated for yourself and your neighbors. And let\xe2\x80\x99s enjoy our concerts in safety and good health!!'

b'We have the tools to fix this. The vaccines really work and have saved so many lives. So grateful to all the scientists who worked so hard on this!  We went from peaking at several thousand deaths a day to a few hundred a day in the US.'

b'The only reason we could even plan this tour was because of how many of our neighbors got vaccinated. Cases, hospitalizations and deaths went down dramatically in highly vaccinated areas. But far too many areas haven\xe2\x80\x99t had enough shots and the Delta variant is running rampant.'
b'Being unvaccinated and/or unmasked at a large indoor gathering is like literally begging to get COVID. Please don\xe2\x80\x99t do that to yourself, your family or your neighbors.'

b'If you plan to be in a large group of people (like hopefully our concert!) in October, you have plenty of time to get fully vaccinated before you come.  Every city and venue will have different rules, but we don\xe2\x80\x99t need the mayor or governor to tell us what\xe2\x80\x99s safe.'
